 <h3>Rule-2 ᐅ </h3>
 <p>Indefinite tense-এর ক্ষেত্রে passive voice-এর structure ᐅ</p>
 <p>1. <b>Present</b>- Object’s subject+ am/is/are+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>She praises me. (Active)</li>
  <li>I am praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <p>2. <b>Past</b>- Object’s subject+ was/were+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>She praised me. (Active)</li>
  <li>I was praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <p>
  3. <b>Future</b>- Object’s subject+ shall be/will be+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object
 </p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>She will praise me. (Active)</li>
  <li>I shall be praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <hr>
 <p>Continuous tense-এর ক্ষেত্রে passive voice-এর structure ᐅ </p>
 <p>
  1. <b>Present</b>- Object’s subject+ am being/is being/are being+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object
 </p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>She is praising me. (Active)</li>
  <li>I am being praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <p>2. <b>Past</b>- Object’s subject+ was being/ were being+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ol>
  <li>She was praising me. (Active)</li>
  <li>I was being praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ol>
 <p>2. <b>Future</b>- Object’s subject+ shall be being/will be being+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>She will be praising me. (Active)</li>
  <li>I shall be being praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <hr>
 <p>Perfect tense-এর ক্ষেত্রে passive voice-এর structure ᐅ </p>
 <p>1. <b>Present</b>- Object’s subject+ has been/ have been+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
 <ul>
  <li>She has praised him. (Active)</li>
  <li>He has been praised by her. (Passive)</li>
 </ul>
 <p>2. <b>Past</b>- Object’s subject+ had been+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
 <h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
<ul>
 <li>She had praised me. (Active)</li>
 <li>I had been praised by her. (Passive)</li>
</ul>
<p>3. <b>Future</b>- Object’s subject+ shall have been/ will have been+ Verb’s past participle+ by+ subject’s object</p>
<h3>Example ᐅ </h3>
<ul>
 <li>She will have praised me. (Active)</li>
 <li>I shall have been praised by her. (Passive)</li>
</ul>
